Repository changes made while resolving exposed failures
- Employer analyst Prompt advanced from 2.0.0 through 2.0.1 to onlyboth.build-answer-evidence-edge@2.0.2.
- 2.0.1 added a final literal-substring and zero-based occurrence validation instruction.
- 2.0.2 explicitly prohibits echoing injected score/rank/hiring terms inside exact_quote and directs the model to cite a different literal, non-prohibited fragment.
- The LIVE acceptance now requires V2, 30 bounded Good/Bad verdicts, all four language dimensions, criterion macro-F1, prohibited-language gates, and same-answer/different-process invariance.
- Process invariance compares decisions, severities, and source block refs. It intentionally does not require model-authored explanations or the exact selected quote span to be byte-identical when both spans validly resolve to the same frozen source.
- OPENAI_EVAL_CASE is an optional eval-only integer selector for focused failure reproduction. With no selector, the full 30-case gate is unchanged.

